instruction:
The modern (ES Module) syntax:

```js
// math.js
export const PI = 3.14159;
export function add(a, b) { return a + b; }
export default function main() { ... }  // default export

// app.js
import main, { PI, add } from './math.js';
//     ^       ^^^^^^^
//     default   named
```

Rules to remember:
- One `export default` per file
- Unlimited named exports
- Named imports use `{ curly braces }`
- Default imports use any name you choose

